If you’re working in HubSpot and have access to HubL, then I’d set them globally via hubl in a js brand object.

Something like the following at the bottom of your base.html file (or whatever you call it in your project):
```&lt;script&gt;
  window.brandColors = {
    primary: '{{ brand_settings.primaryColor.hex }}',
    secondary: '{{ brand_settings.colors[0].hex }}'
  };
&lt;/script&gt;```

